.TH pulsar-shell 1 "Apache Pulsar" "Version 4.1.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pulsar-shell \- Interactive Pulsar command-line shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pulsar-shell
[options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
pulsar-shell provides an interactive command-line interface for working with
Apache Pulsar. It allows executing Pulsar operations interactively without
needing to specify connection details for each command.

.SH OPTIONS
Options vary depending on the shell configuration. Common options include:
.TP
.B --url
Pulsar service URL (e.g., pulsar://localhost:6650)
.TP
.B --admin-url
Pulsar admin service URL (e.g., http://localhost:8080)
.TP
.B --auth-plugin
Authentication plugin class name
.TP
.B --auth-params
Authentication parameters

Run:
.RS
pulsar-shell --help
.RE
for detailed usage and available commands.

.SH EXAMPLES
Start interactive shell:
.RS
pulsar-shell
.RE

Connect to remote cluster:
.RS
pulsar-shell --url pulsar://remote-host:6650
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
pulsar(1), pulsar-admin(1), pulsar-client(1)

